  <description>Petioles glabrous or very short to sparsely long stipitate-glandular. Flowers:
        hypanthium free 0.6–1.5 mm, urceolate; petals greenish, white, or pink, narrower than
        sepals, margins entire or finely dentate. 2n = 14.</description>
  <phenology>Flowering Apr–Jun</phenology>
